t.net/~neoleo/color.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://home.att.net/~neoleo/color.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uazmodion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azmodion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 4:03:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does Cancel magic need to be changed on Sullon?</span><hr size=1> I am getting extremely frustrated with VI. Mez is BUGGED. Strip enchantment is BROKEN. And now, resists are BROKEN. <br>
<br>
Why am I frustrated? It started simply, Mez/bugged and strip enchantment/broken. Mez being bugged, well that sucks but I can deal so long as they are working on fixing strip enchantment. Should be fixed soon right? They knew it was broken in Beta. They should have been working on it since then right? So I wait, and wait and wait. What has it been now 5 weeks? 6 weeks? Who the hell can remember with the countless god damn hours I put in leveling my gimp ass. Days and weeks just start to flow together......Ah patch day! Surely they fixed strip enchantment! By GOD patch man patch!<br>
<br>
....patching....<br>
<br>
After reading the patch message the only thing I could say was.....”WTF?” We have serious PvP problems that need immediate attention and have needed immediate attention for the last 6 god damn weeks and what the fuck is it they have been working on?<br>
<br>
“Characters below 6th level cannot be pick pocketed in any zone”<br>
<br>
Are you fucking kidding me? THIS kind of shit is where the god damn time and resources are going? Who gives a fuck about a level 1 - 5 character and their 2 god damn gold pieces. Anybody who doesn’t fly through levels 1 - 5 in well under 2 hours is an idiot and deserves to have all their pockets picked. We’ve got SERIOUS problems with the PVP system and the attention is going to the game crippling “bug” and “exploit” of pick pocketing level 1 - 5 characters? <br>
<br>
But you know what pisses me off the most, more than the WASTE of time and resources fixing a god damn meaningless problem while not having fixed a big glaring problem that is effecting the foundation of the entire server is simply this, not only are they not fixing the problems but they are fucking it up even more. Consider this. They have a very bad bug in the Mez bug and they have a crippling bug (to the PvP system) with dispel being broken and what have they done since then? They have added more shit to the pile. They changed it so that reds will lose xp to greens but greens have no risk of xp loss. THEN they changed the resists.<br>
<br>
What are the effects of the combination of dispel being broken, the change in xp loss and now the addition of the new resist system?<br>
<br>
“Evil Alliance -3,563 points”<br>
<br>
You think this is a joke? It is funny, hell I was laughing my ass off when I saw this. However, this is no joke, this is an indicator. An indicator of a broken system. While I admit that some of it probably had a little to do with not many evil happened to be actively seeking PvP yesterday while the druids were out in full force testing the new patch, the fact that this happened (negative points) the day the resistance patch was put in is no simple coincidence. <br>
<br>
Anybody who thinks that Druids are not broken on SZ BECAUSE of the SZ bugs (primarily strip enchantment and cancel/nullify magic) are fooling themselves. Right now Druids have a free ride on easy street. They can port all over the map, move through zones quickly, track their prey, attack their prey while protected by countless buffs which CAN NOT BE REMOVED BY THE ENEMY, can DD or DoT, and right now with the new resists can basically stand toe to toe with any other class 20+ levels above them. If they get in trouble they can SoC, heal, gate and evac. It's almost comical. This gravy train the druids have been riding has gotten even sweeter with the addition of the new resist candy. <br>
<br>
I don’t mind the reds taking xp loss to greens. I don’t even mind resists being heavily based on pure number rather than heavily based on level. I don’t necessarily agree with the combination of these two as it gives one side risk free PvP while handing the other an unreasonable risk situation. Perhaps greens allowed to loot coin from reds in lieu of xp loss would be a better solution now with the addition of the new resist system. But I digress. The point is these two things really piss me off with mez being bugged and dispel being broken. Even if they only fixed strip enchantment the free ride the druids have been getting would come to a neck snapping halt, druids would come down to earth with the rest of the classes while still maintaining the edge over most classes that they enjoy on the other PvP servers.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, the PvP coding is fucked up on SZ and instead of fixing it they are piling more potential problems onto it.<br>
<br>
So my vote on this topic? Of course, Strip Enchantment needs fixed YESTERDAY.<br>
<br>
Azmodion<br>
KAAOS / IE <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/unorlalos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norlalos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/01 5:04:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does Cancel magic need to be changed on Sullon?</span><hr size=1> Yes, Cancel magic needs to be fixed.. It should be one of the only spells that can be cast on anyone.. It is both a helpful and hurtful spell, depending on the situation.. <br>
